content.name: Higher Education Provider code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies the Higher Education Provider

content.name: Course code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies each course within a Higher Education/VET Provider (Provider).

content.name: Course name - full
content.definition: The full name of the course

content.name: Course of study type code
content.definition: A code which indicates the type of higher education/VET course

content.name: Special course type code
content.definition: A code which identifies courses of special interest to the department

content.name: Student identification code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies the student within the higher education/VET provider and remains constant from year to year

content.name: Date of birth
content.definition: The day, month and year of birth of the person

content.name: Gender code
content.definition: A code which identifies the sex of a person

content.name: Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander code
content.definition: A code which identifies whether or not the student/applicant identifies herself or himself as being of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander descent

content.name: Location code of term residence
content.definition: The Australian postcode or overseas country code for the residence in which the student lives during the term/period of study, as most recently advised prior to the reference date

content.name: Location code of permanent home residence
content.definition: The Australian postcode or overseas country code of a student's/applicants permanent home residence

content.name: New basis for admission to current course
content.definition: A code which identifies the main criterion used by the Higher Education/VET Provider in granting a student admission to the current course, OR a Higher Education Provider granting an offer/admission to an applicant in a course

content.name: Course commencement date
content.definition: A code which indicates the month and year in which the student commenced the current course for the first time

content.name: Mode of attendance code
content.definition: A code which identifies the mode of attendance by which the student undertakes a unit of study OR the mode of attendance for a preference or offered course as indicated by an applicant

content.name: Type of attendance code
content.definition: A code which identifies whether a student is classified as being a full-time or part-time.

content.name: Academic organisational unit code
content.definition: A code assigned by the Higher Education Provider which uniquely identifies the academic organisational unit providing a unit of study or part of a unit of study.

content.name: Work experience in industry indicator
content.definition: An indicator of whether a unit of study consists wholly of work experience in industry

content.name: Equivalent Full-Time Student Load
content.definition: The EFTSL value representing the student load for a unit of study

content.name: Country of birth code
content.definition: A code representing the country of birth of a student

content.name: Year of arrival in Australia
content.definition: The year in which a student/applicant not born in Australia first arrived in Australia.

content.name: Language spoken at home code
content.definition: A code indicating use of a language other than English at the person's permanent home residence

content.name: Course of study load
content.definition: The aggregated EFTSL value for a course of study, summed across all units of study which meet the academic requirements for the course of study

content.name: Unit of study code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies a unit of study

content.name: Unit of study completion status
content.definition: A code which categorises a students unit of study completion status.

content.name: Citizen/resident indicator
content.definition: A code indicating a student's/applicants citizenship and residence status

content.name: Tertiary entrance score
content.definition: A code indicating the tertiary entrance score obtained by a student commencing an undergraduate award course OR an applicant applying for an undergraduate award course

content.name: Amount paid up front
content.definition: The amount which has been paid for a unit of study or SA-HELP loan

content.name: Total amount charged
content.definition: Amount charged for the unit of study or Student Amenities fee.

content.name: Total exemption granted
content.definition: For students with a commencement date of 2007 or earlier; the percentage of the courses requirements over all its stages for which exemption was granted by the time the requirements of the course were completed.

content.name: Disability
content.definition: An eight-character code indicating responses to three questions about disabilities

content.name: Permanent resident eligibility for HELP assistance
content.definition: A code which identifies details about citizenship, permanent resident status and permanent visa status

content.name: Maximum student contribution indicator
content.definition: A code that indicates which maximum student contribution was used in calculating the student contribution amount

content.name: Course of study name
content.definition: The full name of a course of study

content.name: Person identification code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies a member of staff within the higher education provider

content.name: Student surname
content.definition: The surname of the student/applicant.

content.name: Student given name - first
content.definition: The first given name of the student/applicant

content.name: Student given name - others
content.definition: The other given name or names of the student/applicant

content.name: Student title
content.definition: The title used with a student's name

content.name: Postal address - Part 1
content.definition: The first part of the postal address for correspondence to be sent to the student/applicant

content.name: Postal address - part 2
content.definition: The second part of the postal address for correspondence to be sent to the student/applicant

content.name: Current duties classification type, level and increment code
content.definition: A code which indicates the classification type and level in respect of the current duties of a member of staff at the reference date.

content.name: Postal address - postcode
content.definition: The postcode or overseas country code of the postal address for correspondence to be sent to the student/applicant

content.name: Address of permanent home residence - Part 1
content.definition: The first part of the address for the student's permanent home residence

content.name: Address of permanent home residence - part 2
content.definition: The second part of the address for the student's permanent home residence

content.name: Function code
content.definition: The function being performed in the one work sector and one organisational unit by a member of staff in respect of their current duties

content.name: Address of permanent home residence - postcode
content.definition: The Australian postcode or overseas country code for the student's permanent home residence

content.name: Reporting Year and Period Code
content.definition: The reporting year and period to which the individual data record relates

content.name: Tax file number
content.definition: The tax file number for a student

content.name: Equivalent full-time annual salary current duties
content.definition: The salary level of a member of staff at the reference date, expressed in terms of the annual amount which would be paid to a person performing on a full-time basis the same type of duties as the member of staff and in respect of their current duties

content.name: Variation reason code
content.definition: A numeric code which identifies the reason for a variation

content.name: Combined course of study indicator
content.definition: A code which indicates if a course of study is a combined course of study

content.name: Previous RTP EFTSL
content.definition: The total EFTSL value that has been consumed at previous Higher Education Provider by a student who was enrolled in those Higher Education Provider under the Research Training Program (RTP) and who is enrolled at the current university under the same program.
content.guidance: Field Name: Total previous RTP EFTSL

content.name: Field of education code
content.definition: A code which identifies the field of education to which the course is classified

content.name: Field of education supplementary code
content.definition: A code which identifies the supplementary field of education to which a Combined Course is classified

content.name: Specialisation code
content.definition: A code which identifies a specialisation within a course for which the academic requirements have or will be completed by a student or a group of students

content.name: Discipline code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies the discipline to which a unit of study is classified by the Higher Education Provider/VET provider

content.name: Separation status of Higher Degree Research students
content.definition: The Separation status of a student enrolled in a Higher Degree Research course.

content.name: Postal address - suburb/town
content.definition: Postal Address Suburb/Town for the student/applicant

content.name: Postal address - state code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies the State/Territory or other area in which the student/applicant has their postal address
content.guidance: Field Name: POSTAL ADDRESS STATE CODE

content.name: Postal address - country name
content.definition: A name representing the country of postal address of a student/applicant
content.guidance: Field Name: POSTAL ADDRESS COUNTRY NAME

content.name: Residential address - suburb/town
content.definition: Residential Address Suburb/Town for the student

content.name: Residential address - state
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies the State/Territory or other area in which the student has their residential address
content.guidance: Field Name: RESIDENTIAL ADDRESS STATE CODE

content.name: Residential address - country name
content.definition: A name representing the country of residential address of a student
content.guidance: Field Name: RESIDENTIAL ADDRESS COUNTRY NAME

content.name: Commencing location code of permanent home residence
content.definition: The Australian postcode of a student's permanent home residence in their last year of secondary school for Domestic school leaver commencing an undergraduate or VET course

content.name: Postcode or overseas country code location of Higher Education/VET Provider campus/delivery location
content.definition: The Australian postcode or overseas country code location of the campus/delivery location of the Higher Education/VET Provider where the student is studying this unit.

content.name: Name of suburb/town/locality
content.definition: Name of suburb/town/locality for the student

content.name: Scholarship type code
content.definition: A code which identifies the scholarship type code

content.name: Commonwealth Higher Education Student Support Number (CHESSN)
content.definition: A code, allocated by the department, which uniquely identifies the student within the Higher Education or VET Sector and remains constant from year to year

content.name: Unit of Study Census date
content.definition: A code which indicates the year, month and day which is the Census date of that Unit of Study

content.name: Student Status code
content.definition: A code which indicates the student status for a unit of study

content.name: Highest educational participation prior to commencement
content.definition: A code which indicates the student's or applicants highest educational participation and last year of that participation prior to the first enrolment in the course of study

content.name: Indicative student contribution amount for a Commonwealth supported place
content.definition: The average student contribution amount for a first year student in a Commonwealth supported place.

content.name: Indicative tuition fee for a domestic fee-paying place
content.definition: The average tuition fee for a domestic fee-paying place for a first year student.

content.name: Entry Cut-Off for a Commonwealth Supported place (CSP)
content.definition: A code indicating the previous years lowest entry cut-off required for entry to a CSP for this course at this campus.

content.name: Entry Cut-off for a domestic fee-paying place
content.definition: A code indicating the previous years lowest entry cut-off required for entry to a domestic fee paying place for this course at this campus.

content.name: Overseas student fee for students subject to minimum indicative fee
content.definition: The actual fee to be charged of an overseas student for a course in which a student is enrolled at the Higher Education Provider.

content.name: Highest qualification
content.definition: A code which indicates the highest qualification of a member of staff

content.name: Place of highest qualification
content.definition: A code indicating the higher education provider or type of higher education provider where the studies for which the highest qualification of the member of staff with an academic classification were undertaken

content.name: Appointment Term Code
content.definition: A code which identifies the term of an effective substantive appointment for a member of staff

content.name: Work contract code
content.definition: A code which identifies whether a member of staff has a full-time work contract or fractional full-time work contract in respect of their current duties.

content.name: Current duties term code
content.definition: A code which identifies the term for a member of staffs current duties

content.name: Current duties classification type and level group code
content.definition: A code which identifies the classification type and level group for a member of staff in respect of their current duties

content.name: Organisational unit code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies an organisational unit in which the current duties of a member of staff are being performed

content.name: Work sector code
content.definition: The work sector in which a function is being performed in one organisational unit by a member of staff in respect of their current duties

content.name: Full-time equivalence reference date
content.definition: Staff resources available at the reference date for a function being performed in one work sector and one organisational unit by a member of staff, in respect of their current duties

content.name: Actual full-time equivalence prior year
content.definition: Staff resources expended in the calendar year prior to the reference year, on the one function in the one work sector and the one organisational unit, by types of members of staff of the same sex and who have the same classification type and level group

content.name: Estimated Casual Full-time Equivalent (FTE) - Reference Year
content.definition: The estimated casual FTE staffing level for a reference year

content.name: OS-HELP Study period commencement date
content.definition: A code which indicates the year, month and day on which the student commenced the current six month study period for which they are receiving OS-HELP assistance.
content.guidance: Field Name: OS-HELP STUDY PERIOD COMMENCEMENT-DATE

content.name: QLD Entry Cut-off for a Commonwealth Supported place (CSP)
content.definition: A code indicating the previous years lowest QLD entry cut-off required for entry to a CSP for this course at this campus.
content.guidance: Field Name: QLD ENTRY CUT-OFF CSP

content.name: QLD Entry Cut-off for a domestic fee paying place
content.definition: A code indicating the previous years lowest QLD entry cut-off required for entry to a domestic fee paying place for this course at this campus.

content.name: Campus Location
content.definition: Name of suburb/town/region where the campus is located.

content.name: Commonwealth Scholarship (CS) status code
content.definition: A code which identifies the status of Commonwealth Scholarship (CS).

content.name: HELP debt incurral date
content.definition: A code which indicates the year, month and day on which the student incurred their OS-HELP debt or SA-HELP.

content.name: OS-HELP payment amount
content.definition: The amount of OS-HELP assistance paid to the student in respect of the six month OS-HELP study period.

content.name: Loan fee
content.definition: The loan fee for a unit of study or OS-HELP loan

content.name: Course of study code
content.definition: A code which uniquely identifies an enabling course or a course leading to a higher education award.

content.name: Course of study commencement date
content.definition: A code which indicates the month and year in which the student commenced the current course of study for the first time.

content.name: Course fee type
content.definition: A code which identifies the variety of ways this course is offered to domestic students

content.name: Additional entrance criteria
content.definition: A code which identifies if additional entrance criteria are used when giving consideration to the offer of a place

content.name: Commonwealth Scholarship (CS) termination reason code
content.definition: A code which identifies the reason for the termination of a Commonwealth Scholarship (CS).

content.name: Authorising officer
content.definition: The full name of the authorising officer in the Higher Education/VET Provider

content.name: Commonwealth Scholarship (CS) type code
content.definition: A code which identifies the Commonwealth Scholarship (CS) type

content.name: Summer and Winter school indicator
content.definition: A code indicating if a unit of study is a full-fee summer or winter school unit of study

content.name: Eligibility score
content.definition: The score determined by the institution as the lowest score at which any student, whether Commonwealth Supported or Domestic Fee-paying, be eligible for consideration for this course, excluding special entry.

content.name: OS-HELP country of study code - primary
content.definition: A code representing the primary country at which a student receiving OS HELP assistance will study.

content.name: OS-HELP country of study code - secondary
content.definition: A code representing the second country at which a student receiving OS-HELP assistance will study

content.name: QLD Eligibility score
content.definition: The score determined by the institution as the lowest score at which any student, whether Commonwealth Supported or Domestic Fee paying, be eligible for consideration for this course, excluding special entry.

content.name: Offer Year
content.definition: The year in which a course will be/ is being offered.

content.name: TAC Offer.
content.definition: The admission centre that handles applications for this course

content.name: HELP debt amount
content.definition: The HELP debt amount for a unit of study or SA-HELP loan

content.name: Course campus postcode
content.definition: The Australian postcode or overseas country code of the delivery location/ campus of the Higher Education Provider where the course is being offered

content.name: Credit used value
content.definition: A code which records the cumulative total EFTSL value of credit/RPL used at the reporting date towards the total requirements of the course, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Details of prior study for which credit/RPL was offered
content.definition: A code that records the nature of the study for which credit /RPL was offered, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Field of education of prior VET study for which credit/RPL was offered
content.definition: A code that records details of the field of education of the VET study for which credit/RPL was offered, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Level of education of prior VET study for which credit/RPL was offered
content.definition: A code that records details of the level of the Vocational and Technical Education study for which credit/RPL was offered, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Type of provider where VET study was undertaken
content.definition: A code that denotes the type of Vocational and Technical Education provider with whom the qualification or study for which credit/RPL was offered was undertaken, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Credit Offered Value
content.definition: A code which records the cumulative total EFTSL value of credit/RPL offered at the reporting date towards the total requirements of the course, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Credit /status Higher Education provider code
content.definition: A code indicating the Higher Education Provider where the studies for which the credit/RPL was offered were undertaken, for all students with a commencement date of 2008 or later.

content.name: Scholarship Variation code
content.definition: This code indicates the purpose of the student scholarship record.

content.name: Postal Address Scholarship Postcode
content.definition: The Australian or overseas postcode of the postal address for correspondence to be sent to the student
content.guidance: Field Name: POSTAL ADDRESS SCHOLARSHIP POSTCODE

content.name: Type of Operation of Campus
content.definition: A code which identifies the type of arrangement through which an offshore course is being delivered.

content.name: Principal Mode of Delivery of Offshore Course
content.definition: Principal Mode of Delivery of Offshore Course

content.name: Offshore Delivery Indicator
content.definition: A code which identifies whether a course is delivered partially or fully offshore.

content.name: Year Left School
content.definition: A code that identifies the year in which a commencing domestic student left secondary education.

content.name: Highest educational attainment of parent/guardian 1
content.definition: A code which provides information about the highest educational attainment of the first parent or guardian as identified by the student.

content.name: Highest educational attainment of parent/guardian 2
content.definition: A code which provides information about the highest educational attainment of a second parent or guardian as identified by the student.

content.name: Completion percentage
content.definition: A code that indicates the percentage of a course completion in a joint degree program that is recognised by a provider.

content.name: Joint Degree Partner Higher Education Provider Code
content.definition: A code indicating the partner Higher Education Provider where study in a joint degree is undertaken.

content.name: Areas of study
content.definition: Areas of study included in a Major or Minor as part of a Course of Study.

content.name: Course Search keywords
content.definition: Keywords that provide additional information not included in element E580 - Areas of study.

content.name: OS-HELP Language code
content.definition: A code indicating the language a student is studying in preparation for their OS-HELP study in Asia

content.name: OS-HELP Language study commencement date
content.definition: A date to link a students record for OS-HELP language study with their related OS-HELP record for study in Asia.

content.name: Higher degree by research thesis submission date
content.definition: A code which indicates the year and month in which a higher degree by research student submitted their thesis.

content.name: Higher degree by research completion date
content.definition: A code which indicates the year and month in which a higher degree by research student completed their course of study.

content.name: Higher degree by research end-user engagement code
content.definition: A code which indicates a type of research end-user engagement undertaken by a Higher Degree by Research student.

content.name: Application identification code
content.definition: A code that uniquely identifies an application as assigned by the institution or admissions centre during the application phase

content.name: Application status
content.definition: A code to indicate the current status of the application

content.name: Australian Year 12 result type code
content.definition: A code indicating the type of principal Australian Year 12 qualification (including International Baccalaureate) attempted by an applicant in the current year

content.name: Date offered
content.definition: The date on which an offer of admission in a course was made to an applicant

content.name: Intake date
content.definition: The calendar month and year in which the course will potentially commence for which the applicant has a preference or in which an offer has been made

content.name: International Baccalaureate aggregate score
content.definition: The aggregate score associated with a secondary qualification attempted in the current year by an applicant who has qualified for the award of a International Baccalaureate Diploma or Bilingual International Baccalaureate Diploma

content.name: Preference ordinal position
content.definition: The ordinal position of a preference in the set of preferences of an applicant as at the Reference date

content.name: Response code
content.definition: A code to identify the response of an applicant to an offer of admission to a course

content.name: Sector code
content.definition: A code to identify the sector of a course and the funding source for a higher education course

content.name: Postal address country code
content.definition: A code to indicate the country of the postal address of an applicant
content.guidance: Field Name: POSTAL ADDRESS COUNTRY CODE

content.name: Prior postgraduate course, year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has commenced and/or completed a postgraduate level course (e.g. Higher Doctorate, Doctorate, Masters Degree); and the last year in which the applicant was enrolled in such a course

content.name: Prior degree course, year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has commenced and/or completed a bachelor level course; and the last year in which the applicant was enrolled in such a course

content.name: Prior sub-degree course (HE), year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has commenced and/or completed a sub-degree level course (e.g. Associate degree, Advanced Diploma, Diploma - AQF terminology) at a university, college, or other higher education institute; and the last year in which the applicant was enrolled in such a course

content.name: Prior sub-degree course (VET), year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has commenced and/or completed a sub-degree level course (e.g. Associate degree, Advanced Diploma, Diploma - AQF terminology) through a VET pathway and the last year in which the applicant was enrolled in such a course

content.name: Prior VET award course, year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has commenced and/or completed, a VET award course other than a sub-degree level course (e.g. Associate degree, Advanced Diploma, Diploma AQF terminology); and the last year in which the applicant was enrolled in such a course

content.name: Prior secondary education course through VET sector, year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has completed the final year of secondary education through a Registered Training Organisation (RTO) and the year in which the applicant completed the final year of secondary education

content.name: Prior secondary education course at school, year
content.definition: A code identifying whether an applicant has completed the final year of secondary education at a high school, technical high school, secondary school or secondary college; and the year in which the applicant completed the final year of secondary education
